Nothing beats those warm sunny days when we transition from spring into summer 🌿. This is one of my favourite times of the year, when the grass is green and everything begins to blossom and fill out with all the rich earthly foliage. Having some fresh foliage on the porch is a great way to establish a warm welcome. 

This year I decided to add a mixture of *artificial* cedar trees, green foliage and flowers with a little pop of colour from @decorsveronneau to brighten up our front exterior 🌸. I love the idea of having this beautiful arrangement that is extremely low maintenance and something I can throw together every spring! 
There’s lots of beautiful outdoor planters already blooming at @decorsveronneau… and will be for many seasons to come 😉 

Use code “KASS15” to save on your DV purchases!

4.5 years ago our little 4 month old Scottie, was rushed by ambulance to the Children’s Hospital in London. Scottie under went an emergency surgery and while she recovered, I slept next to her during our week stay in the hospital. Though I didn’t stay in the Ronald McDonald House, there were RMDC amenities within the hospital, directly on our floor that I used daily; showers, food and coffee for the families with sick children. During the duration of the week, I knew I couldn’t leave Scottie’s side for more then 20 minutes, if it was longer, she would wake up frantically and the nurses would attempt to calm her down until I returned. It was a really hard week, but very short compared to so many families staying at the RMH. I’m forever grateful for the compassionate staff and comfort from RMHC ❤️

I’m honoured to share SUNNY SKIES, an inspiring initiative between Ronald McDonald House Charities Southwestern Ontario and @shopgents. This 6 week campaign allows you to purchase or donate from @shopgents where the proceeds will go back to the RMHC SWO ❤️ 

SUNNY SKIES represents positively, encouragement, motivation, and inspiration for families when they need it the most ☼

*follow the link in my stories for more details*

You know I love a good Fall tablescape and this year I partnered with @kspstuff to create a table top full of the perfect items to elevate your Thanksgiving dining experience🍂 
 
Their Opal dinnerware is my favourite! It’s lightweight, durable and made of layered glass which stands out beautifully on my table. The ZWILLING Flatware in rose gold will complement any dinnerware with its clean, elegant and simple design. 
 
The Hemstitch Napkins and Runner are a simple but stylish addition and can be easily used for everyday meals or formal occasions around the table.
 
Lastly, the Trudeau Gala are made of lead free crystalline glass, which looks perfect! Now I’m really excited to host this year 🦃🎃🥧

I’m always looking for unique old pieces to add into our home and the best place to find these treasures is Marketplace! There have been numerous times where I have come across a piece and took too long thinking about it to the point where it sold 🙈 

I have learned my lesson! 

There is something special about an old piece; it’s not mass-produced, it has been around for many years, you wonder about the story behind it and where it’s been… 

I definitely should have hosed this armoire down before bringing it inside, but hey just a few hours of scrubbing 🥲, she was worth it 🤎
